   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>CHAPTER ONE THE ASPIRATION OF THE LORD'S DESIRE THE ONENESS OF HIS BELIEVERS Scripture Reading: John 17:2, 6, 11b, 14-23; Matt 18:19; Acts 1:14; 1 Cor 1:10; Phil 2:2b; Eph 4:4-6; 1 Cor 4:17b; 7:17b; 11:16; 14:34a; Rev 2:7a, 11a, 17a, 29; 3:6, 13, 22; 1:20 OUTLINE The aspiration of the Lord's desire becoming His specific prayer: Before going to the cross.</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>Praying to the Father.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>Earnestly desiring that all His believers be one.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>One in the Father's name and life John 17:2, 6, 11b.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>The Father being the source, and the Father's name indicating the Father Himself the person as the source.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>The Father's life with His nature as the element of oneness in the person of the Father.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>One in the reality of the sanctifying word John 17:14-21.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>The word of God having God Himself as reality.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>God's word of reality sanctifying us from the mixed world unto Himself.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>One in the glory that expresses divinity John 17:22-23.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>The Father's glory indicating the divine life with the divine nature, expressing divinity in splendor.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>The splendid expression of divinity delivers us from ourselves.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>The practice of oneness: The one accord and the oneness in mind, in the church life Matt 18:19; Acts 1:14.</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>Speaking the same thing, being attuned in the same mind and in the same opinion 1 Cor 1:10.</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>Thinking the same thing, having the same love, being joined in soul Phil 2:2b.</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>Based on the attribute of the oneness of the church Eph 4:4-6.</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>According to the apostles' teaching 1 Cor 4:17b; 7:17b; 11:16; 14:34a.</S>
   <S PAR='18' RSNT='1' SNO='18'>According to the same words that the Spirit spoke to the churches Rev 2:7a, 11a, 17a, 29; 3:6, 13, 22.</S>
   <S PAR='19' RSNT='1' SNO='19'>Indicating that the seven churches as the seven golden lampstands are completely identical Rev 1:20.</S>
   </TEXT>
